</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-72_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-73_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-74_ pf-heading-1-h3">Statistics highlighting e-learning impact</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-76_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Research indicates that e-learning can enhance knowledge retention by up to 60%, compared to traditional learning methods. Moreover, a study by the Journal of Medical Internet Research found that web-based education on clinical guidelines improved the practice behaviour of 75% of health professionals surveyed.


